  "text": "This catalog identifies deprecated APIs in Apache Kafka 4.x across configuration constants and exception-handling interfaces. The findings are distributed across 7 key files in the github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489 repository:\n\n**StreamsConfig Configuration Constants (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsConfig.java):**\nThe most significant deprecated config constants include:\n- CACHE_MAX_BYTES_BUFFERING_CONFIG (deprecated since 3.4) - replaced by STATESTORE_CACHE_MAX_BYTES_CONFIG\n- DEFAULT_DESERIALIZATION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG (deprecated since 4.0) - replaced by DESERIALIZATION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG  \n- DEFAULT_PRODUCTION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG (deprecated since 4.0) - replaced by PRODUCTION_EXCEPTION_HANDLER_CLASS_CONFIG\n- DEFAULT_DSL_STORE_CONFIG (deprecated since 3.7) - replaced by DSL_STORE_SUPPLIERS_CLASS_CONFIG\n- ROCKS_DB, IN_MEMORY, and DEFAULT_DSL_STORE - deprecated alongside DEFAULT_DSL_STORE_CONFIG\n- DUMMY_THREAD_INDEX - deprecated integer constant for thread indexing\n- BUFFERED_RECORDS_PER_PARTITION_CONFIG - deprecated buffering configuration\n- DEFAULT_CLIENT_SUPPLIER_CONFIG - deprecated client supplier configuration\n- DEFAULT_TIMESTAMP_EXTRACTOR_CLASS_DOC - deprecated documentation constant\n\n**TopicConfig Constants (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/config/TopicConfig.java):**\n- MESSAGE_DOWNCONVERSION_ENABLE_CONFIG and MESSAGE_DOWNCONVERSION_ENABLE_DOC - both deprecated because down-conversion is not possible in Apache Kafka 4.0 and newer; deprecated for removal in Apache Kafka 5.0\n\n**Exception Handler Interface Methods:**\n\nProductionExceptionHandler (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/errors/ProductionExceptionHandler.java):\n- handle(ProducerRecord<byte[], byte[]>, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - replaced by handle(ErrorHandlerContext, ProducerRecord, Exception)\n- handleSerializationException(ProducerRecord, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - replaced by handleSerializationException(ErrorHandlerContext, ProducerRecord, Exception, SerializationExceptionOrigin)\n\nDeserializationExceptionHandler (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/errors/DeserializationExceptionHandler.java):\n- handle(ProcessorContext, ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]>, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - replaced by handle(ErrorHandlerContext, ConsumerRecord, Exception)\n\n**Exception Handler Implementations:**\n\nDefaultProductionExceptionHandler (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/errors/DefaultProductionExceptionHandler.java):\n- handle(ProducerRecord<byte[], byte[]>, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - uses @Override and @Deprecated annotations, replaced by handle(ErrorHandlerContext, ProducerRecord, Exception)\n\nLogAndFailExceptionHandler (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/errors/LogAndFailExceptionHandler.java):\n- handle(ProcessorContext, ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]>, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - replaced by handle(ErrorHandlerContext, ConsumerRecord, Exception)\n\nLogAndContinueExceptionHandler (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/errors/LogAndContinueExceptionHandler.java):\n- handle(ProcessorContext, ConsumerRecord<byte[], byte[]>, Exception) method (deprecated since 3.9) - replaced by handle(ErrorHandlerContext, ConsumerRecord, Exception)\n\nThe migration path for exception handling shows a consistent pattern: replacing ProcessorContext-based methods with ErrorHandlerContext-based alternatives that provide richer error context metadata. Similarly, configuration constants are being consolidated under new naming schemes (e.g., replacing 'default.*' prefix with simpler alternatives)."
}

