85: /**
86:  * Configuration for a {@link KafkaStreams} instance.
87:  * Can also be used to configure the Kafka Streams internal {@link KafkaConsumer}, {@link KafkaProducer} and {@link Admin}.
88:  * To avoid consumer/producer/admin property conflicts, you should prefix those properties using
89:  * {@link #consumerPrefix(String)}, {@link #producerPrefix(String)} and {@link #adminClientPrefix(String)}, respectively.
90:  * <p>
91:  * Example:
92:  * <pre>{@code
93:  * // potentially wrong: sets "metadata.max.age.ms" to 1 minute for producer AND consumer
94:  * Properties streamsProperties = new Properties();
95:  * streamsProperties.put(ConsumerConfig.METADATA_MAX_AGE_CONFIG, 60000);
96:  * // or
97:  * streamsProperties.put(ProducerConfig.METADATA_MAX_AGE_CONFIG, 60000);
98:  *
99:  * // suggested:
100:  * Properties streamsProperties = new Properties();
101:  * // sets "metadata.max.age.ms" to 1 minute for consumer only
102:  * streamsProperties.put(StreamsConfig.consumerPrefix(ConsumerConfig.METADATA_MAX_AGE_CONFIG), 60000);
103:  * // sets "metadata.max.age.ms" to 1 minute for producer only
104:  * streamsProperties.put(StreamsConfig.producerPrefix(ProducerConfig.METADATA_MAX_AGE_CONFIG), 60000);
105:  *
106:  * StreamsConfig streamsConfig = new StreamsConfig(streamsProperties);
107:  * }</pre>
108:  *
109:  * This instance can also be used to pass in custom configurations to different modules (e.g. passing a special config in your customized serde class).
110:  * The consumer/producer/admin prefix can also be used to distinguish these custom config values passed to different clients with the same config name.
111:  * * Example:
112:  * <pre>{@code
113:  * Properties streamsProperties = new Properties();
114:  * // sets "my.custom.config" to "foo" for consumer only
115:  * streamsProperties.put(StreamsConfig.consumerPrefix("my.custom.config"), "foo");
116:  * // sets "my.custom.config" to "bar" for producer only
117:  * streamsProperties.put(StreamsConfig.producerPrefix("my.custom.config"), "bar");
118:  * // sets "my.custom.config2" to "boom" for all clients universally
119:  * streamsProperties.put("my.custom.config2", "boom");
120:  *
121:  * // as a result, inside producer's serde class configure(..) function,
122:  * // users can now read both key-value pairs "my.custom.config" -> "foo"
123:  * // and "my.custom.config2" -> "boom" from the config map
124:  * StreamsConfig streamsConfig = new StreamsConfig(streamsProperties);
125:  * }</pre>
126:  *
127:  *
128:  * When increasing {@link ProducerConfig#MAX_BLOCK_MS_CONFIG} to be more resilient to non-available brokers you should also
129:  * increase {@link ConsumerConfig#MAX_POLL_INTERVAL_MS_CONFIG} using the following guidance:
130:  * <pre>
131:  *     max.poll.interval.ms &gt; max.block.ms
